    “Personal Information” is information about you that can be used to contact or identify you on-line or off-line. This includes your first name and last name, your date of birth, the city and country of your residence and your email address. “Personal information” may also include a unique device ID for the mobile device upon which you have installed reservouz or the user identifier 'user name' when used in conjunction with your personal information.
    <br />
    “Non-Personal Information” is information that, by itself, cannot be used to identify or contact you personally and can include your gender and your age group and gender preferences as configured in the user settings within
    reservouz. 
    <br />
    This Privacy Policy does not restrict or limit our collection of aggregate information or 
    Non-Personal Information.
    <br />
    Personal information also does not include “aggregate information”. Aggregate information is data we collect about the characteristics and activities of the users of reservouz and used to enhance and improve the services which our product provides, and from which any Personal Information has been removed. Such information may include demographic information, such as your unique user or user identifier (when not matched with or tie to your Personal Information), city of residence, information about your device, software, platform and Internet IP address. We collect aggregate information about the use of the Services to provide the best possible service and allow us to make certain recommendations and internal reports and share such information with our partners about how our customers use the Services so that our partners also understand how people use the Services and they can provide you with an optimal user experience.
    <br />
